Text.SourceString: You’re the new farmer who owns that lot. I used to play there with my friends…
Can me and my friends still go to your farm and play in the mud?
Mom said I can only play near <NPCName>Emma’s</> truck, but I can’t go past the dumpster.
I tried going there again last week, but <NPCName>Emma</> caught me.//Ugh.

Bye!
Mom keeps putting sunscreen on me. Now I’m all slimy.
Oh, look, look! A big seagull!
Aww… It flew away. You missed it!
I’m gonna collect as many pretty shells as I can!
Ooh! Look at that one over there!
<Italic>Dad!</> <PlayerName>$player</> is looking for you!
Hi, hi, hi… Now you gotta talk to my dad.
I’m sleepy…
Are there any cool animals on your farm?
If I was a farmer, I’d spend my days growing trees for animals to live in.
<NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> said my heart is in the right place!//That’s good, right?
I wanna go really, really far and see what other animals they have over there!//It must be so cool.
I read a book about five sisters. And guess what? One of them likes to help animals!//That’s like my dad!
I’m gonna tell Dad about it when I get home.
I wanna go fishing next weekend!
I can’t fish today. I’m very busy. Can’t you see?

I wanna go really really far and see what other animals they have over there! It must be so cool.
<Italic>Mom!</><PlayerName>$player</> is looking for you!
Hi, hi, hi… Now you gotta talk to my mom.//She’s gonna give you some hummus.
My mom and dad are looking for a special bird in the forest today. They want to get it on camera.
I wish I could go with them, but I gotta go to school and stuff.
My favorite bird is the blue jay! What’s yours?
Everyone’s gotta have a favorite bird.
<NPCName>Archie</> and I found a stray cat on the beach yesterday. We tried to catch it, but it ran away.
I wonder if <NPCName>Archie’s</> dad would let him keep an animal.//He’s already got, like, a bazillion pet rocks.
My dad makes really cool videos of wild animals. He knows a lot about them too.
I wanna be like him when I grow up.
Have you tried <NPCName>Emma’s</> tacos before? They’re sooooo good!//I could eat them every single day for the rest of my life.
Do you have any animals on your farm? Cows and sheep and pigs and stuff like that?
Those aren’t the kind of animals my mom and dad make videos of.//They look for wild stuff like snakes and birds and lions.
<NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> taught us some really cool stuff at school yesterday. We learned all about the animals in deserts and tun– tund–
Really cold places. There’s lots of animals that live there. The ground is frozen all year long!
I hope I’m really tall when I grow up. I bet volleyball is a lot easier if you’re super tall.
I saw the coolest bird outside my window today! He was big and green and fluffy and loud!
He was louder than my alarm clock.
I saw this really cool toy at <NPCName>Luke’s</> store last week. I bought it with all my allowance money.
Now I don’t have any money left.
Dad gave me a notebook I can use to write about the birds I see.
I keep it in my bag here, see? It has a pretty bird on the front!
I hope I’m really tall when I grow up. I bet volleyball is a lot easier if you’re super tall.
I saw the coolest bird outside my window today! He was big and green and fluffy and loud!
He was louder than my alarm clock.
Does it seem cold out here to you? I think it’s colder than it was yesterday.
Do you like being a farmer? Is it fun?//I bet it’s a lot of fun.
Mom and Dad say it’s hard work too.//You have to work hard on your farm, and I have to work hard at school!
All the kids in my class are really nice.
One day, I wanna explore the cavern. Mom and Dad say I’m not old enough yet, but I’ll be an adult soon, so I can do it then.
I’m basically already an adult.//I can take care of myself.
See that tree out there? I think Dad said it’s called a birch tree.//Lots of birds like to nest there.
<NPCName>Archie</> got this really cool new video game for his birthday. It lets you pretend to be a farmer.
I guess you don’t have to play that, huh?//You can just go be a farmer on your farm!
I’m reading this cool book series about cats living in the forest.//They form clans and hunt for food and everything.//<portrait=surprised>How cool is that?!
Have you ever seen the wildlife movie called <Italic>Prince of Paws</>?//<portrait=happy>Mom and Dad made that!
It’s all about lions in the savanna.
People get really freaked out when I tell them I’ve touched a crocodile, but I really did it once!//In a big swamp!
It was scary and fun at the same time!
You should go to the library sometime. They have books for literally everything there!
I even found one about blue jays.
Maybe I can help <NPCName>Archie</> at his vet office when we’re both grown-ups.//I want to help animals any way I can.
I’d get really sad if a sick bird came in, though.
Do you think there’s any animals out there we haven’t discovered yet?
What if I discovered a new bird? I’d be super famous!
I wish I could draw better. Sometimes I try to draw the birds I see, but they end up looking like sticks.
It’s okay. The dogs <NPCName>Archie</> draws look like brooms.
I built lots of snowmen and got lots of toys from the Winter market last season.
I hope this year’s Winter is as fun as last year’s!
Mom and Dad told me in the Spring, a bunch of animals come out of hibernation.
They stop sleeping and come out for food.//Everything’s waking up for Spring!
A bumblebee got stuck in my room yesterday. It almost stung me too!
That wouldn’t have happened if it was still Winter.
I don’t wanna do my reading. It’s too hot out here to do anything.
Why is it so hot? It keeps getting hotter every day.
How many days until Winter starts?
I wonder if <NPCName>Archie</> wants to go swimming today.
I found a spider in my room yesterday, but I let him stay there.//Fall is supposed to be a spooky time of year, anyway!
Plus he eats bugs and stuff.
The crunchy leaves outside are so much fun to jump in!//Me and <NPCName>Archie</> and Taco take turns making piles and jumping in them.
I wanna get a new book to read.//What should I get?
How about something spooky with animals?//That sounds like fun.
<Italic>Woo-hoo!</> Bring on the snow and cold! Happy Winter!
There’s so many fun things that happen in Winter.//You get to build snowmen, visit the Winter market, curl up inside with a big blankie…
I mean, a big blanket. Blankies are what little kids have.
I wish it were always this cold. Maybe I should move to somewhere colder when I grow up.
I hear Pokyo gets really cold in Winter.
I keep getting– Ah!
I keep getting rain in my eyes.
Where’s Mom and Dad? I wanna go home. It’s too wet out here.
I’m glad I’m in here. I don’t wanna get all wet in the rain.
Are there any cartoons on TV? I can’t play outside if it’s raining like this.
<NPCName>Archie</> said he was gonna visit Taco today.//I wonder if he went in the rain.
Are the birds gonna be okay in the wind?//It’s blowing so hard!
The ocean looks so angry!//I don’t wanna go swimming right now.
Can you see anything in this storm?
Well, I guess there’s lightning, but I wish the sun was out like normal.
What if you climbed to the tippy-top of the island in this storm? I bet the view would be really cool.
Dad says you’d get hit by lightning, though.
A tree keeps hitting the side of our house, and it sounds creepy.//I wish it wasn’t windy anymore.
Snow day! <Italic>Yay!</>
Maybe <NPCName>Archie</> will have a snowball fight with me later.
I love watching the snow from in here! It’s so white and fluffy and pretty.
Is the snow still going? It’s gonna be piled up so high tomorrow!
Do you think <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> will close school tomorrow if there’s enough snow outside?
Maybe <NPCName>Archie</> and I can cover the front door in snow so no one can get in.
[<NPCName>Zoe</> is busy with her arts and crafts.]
Sometimes <NPCName>Archie</> asks silly questions just to make <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> confused. It’s really funny.
“<NPCName>Mr. Barnes</>, what’s a cow?”
<NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> actually watched <Italic>Prince of Paws</> once!//It’s so cool he watched something my parents made!
I hope one day he watches one of my wildlife movies too.
Dad? Are there any good cartoons on?
Oh, you’re not Dad. Do you know if there’s any good cartoons on right now?
Shh! I’m learning about animals.
It’s such a nice day outside, right?
Did you know there’s like ten thousand different kinds of birds out there?
I learned that in a book.
It’s nice to not be in school. I get tired of going there every day.
Mom and Dad say school ends when you grow up, but I don’t know if I believe them.
Are you gonna tell my mom I’ve been trying to sneak to the recycling center after school?
Ugh… I don’t trust you.//You know too much.
I like to go to the library because <NPCName>Millie</> always has a plate of cookies.
If I read a book and talk about it with her afterward, she’ll give me a cookie.
I read so many books and got so many cookies this week!
I’m very careful with animals. Dad said wild animals get scared easily, so we have to show we’re not going to hurt them.
Oh! I saw a cool bird on my walk to school this morning.
I don’t know what it was. But I bet my dad would know!//He knows everything.
I’m very careful with animals. Dad said wild animals get scared easily, so we have to show we’re not going to hurt them.
I want a pet lizard like <NPCName>Millie’s</>. The ones that live at home always hide from me.
I can’t wait until I’m big and tall like Dad so I can go to the forest by myself.
I wonder if I’ll ever grow that big or if I’ll stay small forever.
<NPCName>Archie</> has the coolest monocular!//He said he found it in the forest.
So lucky! I wanna go to the forest and find things too!
I wanna adopt so many animals when I grow up so that Bonbon can have tons of friends!
I can’t wait until I’m big and tall like Dad so I can go to the forest by myself.
I wonder if I’ll ever grow that big or if I’ll stay small forever.
Our house has lizards that go in and out. But Dad said we can’t keep any.
They’re so cute.//I wanna pet them.
I wanna adopt so many animals when I grow up so that Bonbon can have tons of friends!
I wanna travel a lot when I grow up. I can take my bird notebook with me and draw every bird in the whole world.
That’s what my parents do. They travel to see cool birds and other animals.
Yesterday, I scared away a bird my dad and I were watching.//I felt really bad, but he wasn’t mad. He said it happens sometimes.
I wish it would happen less.
My dad found the coolest bird in the forest the other day.//<portrait=normal>He’s so good at finding animals!
That’s why he’s so good at his job.
Should I go to the beach today? Or to the park?//<portrait=annoyed>Or maybe Emma’s Taco Truck? Ugh, I can’t decide where I want to go!
I wish there were three Zoes so I could go everywhere!
Making that video was sooooo worth it. Now I know exactly what I’m gonna do when I grow up.
I can’t wait to be a professional bird-watcher!
This lesson is so boooooring. I don’t wanna learn about the water cycle.//I wanna learn about animals.
I almost showed our bird movie to <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</>, but I wanna keep it a secret for now.
I wonder if he saw the bird too.
Our last test was about animals, so I did super well on it! I even beat <NPCName>Valentina</>.
She was all mad and everything. Oops!
I haven’t seen that bird since we finished the movie. I wonder if it flew somewhere else.//There’s nothing about it in the library either.
I hope I see it again one day.
